Fork System called  
- used for creating a new process (child process) 
- it runs concurrently with the process that makes the fork() call (parent process)
- after creation of the new child, both processes withh execute the next instuction 
- they run in separate memory spaces 
- takes no arguments 
- returns an integer value
    - positive value: returns of parent process (contains PID of child process)
    - zero: returned to the child process 
    - negative value: child creation was unsuccessful 
    